        "text": "Right — that's the core issue: `wine64-preloader` has the window registered (macOS sees it, `Cmd+Tab` may even list it) but nothing is drawn on screen. This is the Wine **virtual-desktop** rendering quirk — I saw `explorer.exe /desktop` (pid 34133) in the process list, which means Wine is running in *virtual desktop mode*: it draws one big container window and paints the launcher inside it. If that container lands off-screen or on a phantom Space, everything inside is invisible.\n\nLet me diagnose the window's actual state and try to force it back onto the visible screen.",
